This article is a proclamation from the President of the United States declaring October 6, 2014, as Child Health Day. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of ensuring the health and well-being of children and highlights the Affordable Care Act's role in expanding access to quality healthcare for children. It also mentions the Let's Move! initiative by First Lady Michelle Obama, which promotes healthy choices and physical activity for children. The article calls for efforts to address issues like childhood obesity and air pollution to protect the health of future generations. The proclamation concludes by urging families, educators, healthcare professionals, and all levels of government to prioritize the health of America's children.